    "reasoning": "The FSM needs to detect start bit, data bits (LSB first), and stop bit. States: IDLE, START, DATA, STOP. Start when in IDLE and in=0. Wait for 10 cycles (start bit duration), verify stop bit is 1. If stop invalid, wait until stop bit found before next. Use counters for data bits. Registered outputs. Signals: state, counter, data_reg. Start bit detection in IDLE state. If start bit valid (after debounce), proceed to DATA state. Shift in 8 bits. Check stop bit. If stop error, loop until stop bit received. All signals initialized. Combinational for next state logic, sequential for state updates. Data storage via shift register. Done asserted after stop bit verified.",
    "module": "module TopModule (input clk, input reset, input in, output done);\n  logic [2:0] state, next_state;\n  logic [3:0] counter;\n  logic [7:0] data_reg;\n  logic done_reg;\n  localparam IDLE = 3'b000,\n            START = 3'b001,\n            DATA = 3'b010,\n            STOP = 3'b011,\n            ERROR = 3'b100;\n\n  // State register\n  always @(posedge clk) begin\n    if (reset) state <= IDLE;\n    else state <= next_state;\n  end\n\n  // Data and counter registers\n  always @(posedge clk) begin\n    if (reset) begin\n      data_reg <= 8'h0;\n      counter <= 4'h0;\n      done_reg <= 0;\n    end else begin\n      if (state == DATA) begin\n        data_reg <= {in, data_reg[7:1]}; // LSB first\n        counter <= counter + 1;\n      end else if (state == STOP) begin\n        counter <= 0;\n        if (in) done_reg <= 1;\n        else done_reg <= 0; // Stop error\n      end else begin\n        data_reg <= data_reg;\n        counter <= 0;\n        done_reg <= 0;\n      end\n    end\n  end\n\n  // Next state logic\n  always @(*) begin\n    next_state = state;\n    case (state)\n      IDLE: next_state = (in == 0) ? START : IDLE;\n      START: next_state = (counter == 4'd9) ? DATA : START;\n      DATA: next_state = (counter == 4'd8) ? STOP : DATA;\n      STOP: next_state = (in == 1) ? IDLE : ERROR;\n      ERROR: next_state = (in == 1) ? IDLE : ERROR;\n      default: next_state = IDLE;\n    endcase\n  end\n\n  // Done output\n  assign done = done_reg;\n\nendmodule"
